               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360404-name-840" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-840" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-840" type="surname" value="STEVENTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360404-name-840" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM STEVENTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Little Warner-street. The prisoner was employed to clean my boots and clothes—he did not live in house—he occasionally came into my room in the morning to take my clothes to brush—on the 27th of March I do not know whether he came into my room, as I was asleep—I went to bed about twelve o'clock, on Saturday night, leaving my watch in my fob, some gold in my waistcoat-pocket, and some silver in the trowsers—when I got up I missed my watch and money a sovereign and three shillings—the prisoner did not come to me that morn<lb></lb>ing—I suspected him, and gave information—this is my watch (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>)—he had been nearly two months in my service.</p>
